      "text": "# The law of property Act 1925"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "4ee1591a46d596cc0af5f83778f81c87",
      "text": "The [[Law of Property Act 1925]], which still forms the core of English property law, has two provisions for common land:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "013aaec74478432942334a7c6039d1b4",
      "text": "* Section 193 gave the right of the public to \"air and exercise\" on Metropolitan commons and those in urban districts and boroughs. This constituted about one fifth of the commons, but did not give this right to commons in rural areas, which had to wait for the 2000 CROW act."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f1389af8dacc45d0c5bff090ad50e434",
      "text": "* Section 194 restricted the enclosure of commons, which would now require Ministerial consent - [http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Geo5/15-16/20/contents Law of Property Act 1925]"
    },
