      "text": "# Commons Registration Act 1965"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "32870a6e6b0dca7336d59eaabbeb75bd",
      "text": "The UK government regularised the definitions of common land with the [[Commons Registration Act 1965]], which established a register of common land - [http://www.opsi.gov.uk/RevisedStatutes/Acts/ukpga/1965/cukpga_19650064_en_1 Commons Registration Act 1965]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "efcd2615878f798e2c6fb70d5ffaf1eb",
      "text": "Not all commons have owners, but all common land by definition is registered under 1965 Commons registration Act, along with the rights of any commoners if they still exist. The registration authorities are the County Councils, and when there is no ownership, a local council, such as a parish council ([[parish councils in England]]) is normally given guardianship by vesting the property under the Act (section 8)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f3f82acb520b5aec3ba0f63ac36f5fd2",
      "text": "An online database of registered common land was compiled by DEFRA in 1992-93 as part of a survey of the condition and wildlife of commons.<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/218756/common-land.xls DEFRA Database of registered common land in England compiled 1992-93]</ref> The official up to date Registers of common land are held by the Commons Registration Authorities."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2fea5eff787d668cef4749c58fe9bfdc",
      "text": "The following registration information is held:<ref>Cumbria CC website 2014</ref>"
    },
